definitions.definition: The point of the celestial sphere, directly opposite the zenith; inferior pole of the horizon; point of the celestial sphere directly under the place of observation.
The lowest point; time of greatest depression.
The axis of a projected conical shadow; the direction of the force of gravity at a location; down.
definitions.example: The nadir of the sun is the axis of the shadow projected by the Earth.

definitions.definition: An empty box added beneath a full one in a beehive to give the colony more room to expand or store honey.
To extend (a beehive) by adding an empty box at the base.
To continuously remind or complain to (someone) in an annoying way, often about insignificant or unnecessary matters.
To bother with persistent thoughts or memories.
definitions.example: The notion that he forgot something nagged him the rest of the day.

definitions.definition: To bother or disturb persistently in any way.
definitions.example: a nagging north wind

definitions.definition: The action of the verb nag.
Causing persistent mild pain, or annoyance.
A female deity (nymph) associated with water, especially a spring, stream, or other fresh water.
The aquatic larva (nymph) of a dragonfly or damselfly.
Any of various aquatic plants of the genus Najas.
The thin, horny plate at the ends of fingers and toes on humans and some other animals.
definitions.example: When I'm nervous I bite my nails.

definitions.definition: The basal thickened portion of the anterior wings of certain hemiptera.
The terminal horny plate on the beak of ducks, and other allied birds.
The claw of a bird or other animal.

A spike-shaped metal fastener used for joining wood or similar materials. The nail is generally driven through two or more layers of material by means of impacts from a hammer or other device. It is then held in place by friction.
A round pedestal on which merchants once carried out their business, such as the four nails outside The Exchange, Bristol.
An archaic English unit of length equivalent to 1/20 of an ell or 1/16 of a yard (2 1/4 inches or 5.715 cm).
To fix (an object) to another object using a nail.
definitions.example: He nailed the placard to the post.

definitions.definition: To drive a nail.
definitions.example: He used the ax head for nailing.

definitions.definition: To stud or boss with nails, or as if with nails.
To catch.
To expose as a sham.
To accomplish (a task) completely and successfully.
definitions.example: I really nailed that test.

definitions.definition: To hit (a target) effectively with some weapon.
Of a male, to engage in sexual intercourse with.
To spike, as a cannon.
To nail down: to make certain, or confirm.
A naive person; a greenhorn.
Lacking worldly experience, wisdom, or judgement; unsophisticated.
Not having been exposed to something.
(of art) Produced in a simple, childlike style, deliberately rejecting sophisticated techniques.
Intuitive; designed to follow the way ordinary people approach a problem.
Lack of sophistication, experience, judgement or worldliness; artlessness; gullibility; credulity.
Bare, not covered by clothing.
definitions.example: She was as naked as the day she was born.

definitions.definition: Lacking some clothing; clothed only in underwear.
Glib, without decoration, put bluntly.
definitions.example: The naked facts lay there on the table, enclosed within the files.

definitions.definition: Characterized by the nakedness of the people concerned or to whom the described noun is attributed.
Unarmed.
Unaided, unaccompanied.
Unprotected, uncovered; (by extension) without a condom.
definitions.example: I entered her naked and came in her too.

definitions.definition: (of a derivative contract) Where the writer (seller) does not own the underlying asset to cover the contract.
definitions.example: a naked put, a naked call

definitions.definition: Resourceless, poor, lacking means.
(with “of”) Lacking or devoid of something.
Blank, clean, empty.
(of land, rocks, or plants) Barren, having no foliage, unvegetated.
Uncomfortable or vulnerable, as if missing something important.
definitions.example: I feel naked without my mobile phone.

definitions.definition: (of food or other consumer products) Without any additives, or without some component that would usually be included.
definitions.example: Naked Bacon (a brand without nitrates or phosphates)

definitions.definition: Of a singularity, not hidden within an event horizon and thus observable from other parts of spacetime.
To make naked; to bare.
Any nounal word or phrase which indicates a particular person, place, class, or thing.
definitions.example: I've never liked the name my parents gave me so I changed it at the age of twenty.

definitions.definition: Reputation.
An abusive or insulting epithet.
definitions.example: Stop calling me names!

definitions.definition: A person (or legal person).
Those of a certain name; a race; a family.
A unique identifier, generally a string of characters.
An investor in Lloyds of London bearing unlimited liability.
Authority.
definitions.example: Halt in the name of the law!

definitions.definition: (ditransitive) To give a name to.
definitions.example: One visitor named Hou Yugang said he was not too concerned about climate change and Baishui’s melting.

definitions.definition: To mention, specify.
definitions.example: He named his demands.

definitions.definition: To identify as relevant or important
definitions.example: naming the problem

definitions.definition: To publicly implicate.
definitions.example: The painter was named as an accomplice.

definitions.definition: To designate for a role.
definitions.example: My neighbor was named to the steering committee.

definitions.definition: (Westminster system politics) To initiate a process to temporarily remove a member of parliament who is breaking the rules of conduct.
Any of several types of true yam (Dioscorea) used in Caribbean Spanish cooking.
One who is named after another or for whom another is named.
(by extension) A ship or a building that is named after someone or something.
A person with the same name as another.
To name (somebody) after somebody else.
An effeminate man, especially a homosexual.
A measure of time equal to one billionth of a second. Abbreviation: ns
A serviette; a (usually rectangular) piece of cloth or paper used at the table for wiping the mouth and hands for cleanliness while eating.
A nappy (UK), a diaper (American).
A small scarf worn on the head by Christian women (chiefly Roman Catholic and Eastern Orthodox) when entering a church, as a token of modesty.
A sanitary napkin.
A former 40-franc gold coin issued by France.
A form of solitaire.
A short period of sleep, especially one during the day.
A soft or fuzzy surface, generally on fabric or leather.
The common direction, on some kinds of fabric, of the hairs making up the pile.
definitions.example: If the fabric has a nap, make sure all pieces are cut with the nap going the same direction.

definitions.definition: A type of bet in British horse racing, based on the experts' best tips.
A card game in which players take tricks; properly Napoleon.
A bid to take five tricks in the card game Napoleon.
(dialectal, Northern England, Scotland) A cup, bowl.
The franc germinal: a 20-franc gold coin issued under Napoleon.
Other subsequent 20-franc coins, notes, or values.
(usually admiringly derogatory) A person resembling Napoleon Bonaparte, in having come to dominate an area or sphere of activity through ruthlessness or illegality as well as surpassing ability.
Clipping of Napoleon boot: a form of topboot worn by officers during the Napoleonic Wars.
Clipping of Napoleon gun: a 12-pounder cannon first used by the Second French Empire.
A 19th-century five-card trick-taking game simplified from euchre.
Clipping of Napoleon bigarreau: a variety of the white-fleshed bigarreau cherry; a variety of cherry tree bearing such fruit.
(originally United States slang) Clipping of Napoleon cake: another name for a millefeuille pastry.
(alcohol) Clipping of Napoleon brandy: any excellent brandy; a serving of such a brandy.
(pastries) A multi-layered stacked pastry
